==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Satinet
<hw>Sat`i*net"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F., fr.
<ets>satin</ets>. See <er>Satin</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A thin
kind of satin.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A kind of cloth made of cotton warp and woolen
filling, used chiefly for trousers.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Satinette</ent>⟦br⟧
